The death toll from the unrest in South Africa has risen to 212. A total of 1,692 people were arrested in connection with looting and violence. PRETORIA - On Friday, Acting Minister in the Presidency, Khumbudzo Nthsavheni confirmed the death toll from the unrest in South Africa has risen to 212. READ: Sabotage in KZN | No evidence of SSA members being involved - Dlodlo A total of 180 people were killed in KwaZulu-Natal and 32 in Gauteng. Police arrested 1,692 people in connection with looting and violence.